Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Chicken Massaman Curry in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Zesty Jasmine Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @carrot{1}(peeled and sliced into 1cm thick rounds).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the carrot and fry until starting to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

While the carrot cooks, pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Chicken Massaman Curry ==

Once the carrot has softened, stir in the garlic and @Massaman Curry Paste{50%g}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @Coconut Milk{200%ml} and @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}, then stir through the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Peanut Butter{30%g} until well combined.

Bring to the boil.

Stir the @Diced Chicken Thigh{210%g} into the sauce and bring back to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @Lime{1/2}(zested and cut into wedges) into wedges.

For the last ~{2%mins} of cooking, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot.

== To Serve ==

When the curry is ready, remove from the heat. Stir in the @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and a squeeze of lime juice, along with a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Serve the zesty rice in #bowls{} with the chicken curry on top and a lime wedge alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!